### Evaluation commands

- **OS**
    - `uname -v`
- **Modify hostname**
    - `sudo nano /etc/hostname`
    - `sudo nano /etc/hosts`
    
    - `sudo reboot`cd
- **user and group:**
    - `getent group`
    - `getent group <name of the group>`
    - `cat  /etc/passwd # show all users`
    - `sudo groupdel <name of group>`
    - `sudo userdel <name of user>`
- **sudo**
    - Show the application of the rules imposed for sudo by the subject. → path → `/var/log/sudo` and `nano /etc/sudoers.d/sudo_config`
    - `sudo nano hello42` and than check the log: `cat sudo_config`
- **UFW**
    - `sudo service ufw status` or `dpkg -s ufw`
    - `sudo ufw status` `numbered`
    - `sudo ufw delete <num_rule>`
- **ssh**
    - `which ssh`
    - `sudo service ssh status`
    - verify that using ssh with the root is not allowed: `ssh root@localhost -p 4242`, allowed with `ssh username@localhost -p 4242`
- **Crontab**
    - `sudo crontab -u root -e`
    - `sudo /etc/init.d/cron stop`-> make the script stop running when the server has started, but without modifying the script
    - `sudo /etc/init.d/cron start`
- **password**
    - `nano /etc/login.defs` - max_day
    - `nano /etc/pam.d/common-password`
    - `passwd -S <name of the username or root>`
    - `sudo` `passwd -S <name of the username or root>`